OL,6,     FBrazil v Haiti (Kick-off 1.30am).
OL,7,     FMark Pougatch presents coverage of
OL,8,     Fthe Group C match at Philadelphia
OL,9,     FStadium in the USA. Brazil were
OL,10,     Fsecond best for most of their
OL,11,     Fopener against Morocco, but came
OL,12,     Faway with a 1-1 draw, while Haiti
OL,13,     Fperformed admirably in a 1-0
OL,14,     Fdefeat to Scotland. Brazil have
OL,15,     Fregistered large victories in the
OL,16,     Ftwo previous encounters between
OL,17,     Fthese nations, claiming a 6-0 win
OL,18,     Fin an international friendly in
OL,19,     F2004, and more recently a 7-1
OL,20,     Ftriumph in the group stage of the
OL,21,     F2016 Copa America, which also took
OL,22,     Fplace in the United States, and
